# HALT-bug (PC double-read) -- CORRECTED, Gambatte-verified model.
#
# STATUS: correct CPU model, but NET-NEGATIVE on the current byte-exact engine
# (+1 overall: 514 -> 515). Fixes 8 register-anomaly halt tests; breaks 10
# m0stat tests that depend on the orthogonal PPU STAT-mode-timing root (the
# documented mode-3-length / m0-dispatch-cc bug). The 10 break because they were
# *accidentally passing*: the old halt-sleep re-synchronized the CPU to the IRQ
# wakeup and masked the PPU timing error. RE-APPLY this patch AFTER the PPU
# mode-0-time predictor is ported (project memory: ppu-mode3-length-lever).
#
# Model == Gambatte cpu.cpp case 0x76 exactly:
#   - HALT-bug fires whenever (IE & IF) != 0, IME-INDEPENDENT (no !ime gate).
#   - When it fires: set cpu.halt_bug; next opcode fetch reads the byte after
#     HALT WITHOUT incrementing PC, so that byte executes twice.
#   - service_interrupt() clears cpu.halt_bug (Gambatte Interrupter::interrupt
#     "undo prefetch"): EI;HALT services the IRQ and discards the anomaly.
#
# Verified cc-exact vs cctracer (both fire the bug; my engine reproduces it):
#   noime_ifandie_m2int_m0stat_1 (HALT@0x1006): 0x1006->0x1007->0x1007->0x1008
#   late_m0irq_halt_m0stat_scx2_3a (HALT@0x1035): 0x1035->0x1036->0x1036->0x1037
#   late_m0irq_halt_m0stat_scx2_4a (HALT@0x1036): 0x1036->0x1037->0x1037->0x1038
# Residual divergence on those 10 is the downstream STAT-mode read value (PPU),
# NOT the HALT logic.
#
# FIXES (8): noime_ifandie_halt_sra(outF1), noime_ifandie_halt_lda_3c(out3F),
#   late_m0irq_halt_dec_scx2_2 / _scx3_2 (out6) -- all dmg+cgb.
# BREAKS (10, PPU-timing): late_m0irq_halt_m0stat_scx2_3a/_scx2_4a/_scx3_3a/
#   _scx3_4a (out0), noime_ifandie_m2int_m0stat_1 (out0) -- all dmg+cgb.
# NO collateral outside the halt/ directory.
#
